ETYMOLOGY. — The new species is named in honor of Jean-François Leroy (1915-1999), whose taxonomic studies have enhanced the knowledge of the flora of Madagascar , especially in the Rubiaceae and the Meliaceae . Leroy described ten of the 12 currently recognized species of
Astrotrichilia
, including four that were co-authored with Lescot ( Leroy & Lescot 1996 ;
Madagascar Catalogue 2019
).
